Frank R. - 

Yes, I have personally divided them as ghosts and spirits, as spirits 
come from the light.  I believe when we die we can choose to remain 
earthbound (not good - ghosts), or we can proceed unto the light, 
loved ones and a life-review...which is part of the cleansing process 
you implied.  That is a cleaned up person or &quot;spirit.&quot;  A ghost still 
has the mis-thinking or darkness within, covering over the light of 
truth.

With that same idea, isn&#39;t it interesting that the gospels mention 
Jesus casting out &quot;unclean spirits?&quot;

LC
http://www.AngelsGhosts.com

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Frank Ratka &lt;warrior18eii@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; I think their is a difference between ghosts and spirits, though it 
is a small one. A ghost is a spirit that is earthbound or still 
thinking like a human with all of our self-imposed limitations. A 
spirit is an entity who has learned to shed it&#39;s human persona.
&gt; 
&gt; Regards,
&gt; 
